&lt;p&gt;The Associate Benefits Partner supports the delivery of core benefits operations through accurate data management, standardized process execution, and timely employee and stakeholder support. This person will ensure compliant, high-quality administration across health, welfare, and retirement programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute day-to-day benefits processes: enrollments, qualifying life events, dependent verification, status changes, terminations, COBRA administration, and eligibility updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to employee and manager inquiries on benefits programs, policies, enrollment, payroll deductions, and vendor processes within established SLAs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records in HRIS, payroll, and vendor systems to ensure data integrity and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HR Operations (HRIS, Payroll, Central HR Ops) and vendors to resolve routine benefits issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support benefits-related onboarding and off-boarding activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with compliance activities, including audits, reporting, documentation retention, and reconciliation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and escalate complex or non-standard issues to Benefits Partners or senior team members as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain benefits guides, SharePoint site, onboarding course, and internal process documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in training, knowledge-sharing, and continuous improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support special projects, vendor implementations, or process improvement efforts as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of experience in benefits or HR administration, preferably in a corporate environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or related field (or equivalent experience).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with HRIS and/or benefits administration platforms (e.g., Workday, SAP, ADP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundational understanding of employee benefits programs and applicable regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, customer service, and organizational skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and commitment to data accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer service mindset with professional communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to follow standardized processes and maintain compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundational knowledge of medical, dental, vision, retirement, and wellness programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and time management skills; able to manage multiple priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic analytical and problem-solving skills with appropriate escalation judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with HRIS, benefits platforms, and Microsoft/Google productivity tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discretion in handling confidential employee information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative and relationship-oriented across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
