&lt;p&gt;The Home Data Science team is looking for an Associate Data Scientist to join our growing applied ML practice. This is a role for someone who wants to move fast, learn from strong technical mentors, and own real work from the start. You&#39;ll contribute to ML and AI solutions that drive measurable business outcomes across our Home Services partners, including work in telecommunications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll be embedded in a collaborative team that values technical depth, clear thinking, and getting things across the finish line. Expect hands-on work, direct feedback, and genuine investment in your development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role requires a hybrid schedule and will be based in our South Charlotte, NC Headquarters (Tuesday through Thursday) and work fully remotely on Mondays and Fridays each week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Curious how Home fits into Red Ventures? &lt;a class=&quot;in-cell-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.redventures.com/portfolio/rv-home-client-services&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Click here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development and deployment of ML/AI solutions in production environments, with a focus on building reliable, well-tested code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work across the full data lifecycle, from pulling and cleaning data to building models and tracking their downstream impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take solutions built by our platform teams and deliver them customized to individual clients and partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, and business stakeholders to understand problem context and translate it into well-scoped data science work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate progress, risks, and results clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in code reviews and pair programming sessions that meet team development standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build working knowledge of key business KPIs and how model outputs connect to them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take on clearly scoped tickets and small projects independently, escalating blockers early&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop proficiency across common ML techniques, model deployment practices, and the tools and platforms the team uses day-to-day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master&#39;s degree in a quantitative field (Computer Science, Statistics, Economics, Mathematics, or similar) OR Bachelor&#39;s degree 1-2 years professional experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundational understanding of core data science techniques such as classification, regression, clustering, and when to apply each&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Python and SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Generative AI tools such as Claude Code, Codex, or Cursor, Gemini, Langchain, Mastra, Open AI or similar tools.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with model deployment and ML operations concepts, including version control, CI/CD, and job orchestration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical instincts for exploratory data analysis and an ability to assess both technical model performance and its business impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative working style with genuine curiosity about how the business works and what drives value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior internship, research, or project experience applying ML to real-world problems is a strong plus; experience with Databricks or cloud platforms (AWS) is a bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
