&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and art direct adult nonfiction trade books and print products from concept through production, ensuring each title is visually distinctive and on-brand with Lonely Planet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strategic book design systems tailored to the category, content, and target consumer of each product, informed by current design and market trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with editors, producers, and cross-functional stakeholders to deliver best-in-class designs that inspire and excite travel lovers worldwide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present work to cross-functional teams with clear, audience-grounded design rationale and confident creative storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source and select stock imagery that is creative, accurate, and aligned with each title&#39;s visual direction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Art direct freelance designers and illustrators, managing outside creative talent from brief to final delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and manage print-ready design files and assets with thorough attention to production specifications and quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience designing adult nonfiction trade books and paper products, with a portfolio of commercially published titles — portfolio is required and must include published adult nonfiction trade books&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep fluency in Adobe InDesign, including type styles, parent pages, link management, and importing coded manuscripts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thorough understanding of print production workflows and experience preparing files for commercial print&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-house publishing experience strongly preferred — you understand how editorial and design teams work together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to analyze market and design trends and translate insights into product opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience art directing freelance designers and illustrators; an existing freelancer network is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communicator who can manage multiple projects simultaneously, set clear expectations, and collaborate across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Genuine passion for travel and an enthusiasm for books that comes through in your work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Total Cash Compensation Range:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;$81,250 - $118,000 per year &lt;/em&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;*&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To qualify for NYC Comp Range, NYC applicants will be required to work a hybrid schedule of Tuesday - Thursday in our NYC office with Mondays and Fridays remote.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
