&lt;p&gt;Curious how Shared Services fits into Red Ventures? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.redventures.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Click here&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Red Ventures is looking for a deal-oriented, execution-focused Corporate Development Associate to join our multi-faceted Corporate Development team. This is a high-volume, high-accountability role built for someone who thrives on owning the work. You will be the engine behind our M&amp;amp;A, investments, capital structuring, and inorganic growth decisions: vetting targets, keeping workstreams on track, guiding cross-functional teams through end-to-end processes, building financial models, and making sure leadership has what they need to make fast and informed decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work across transactions ranging from $10M-$2B across technology, financial services, media, telecom, education and travel. Expect significant variety, a fast pace, and real accountability from day one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and own first-draft financial models, including income statement, balance sheet, and cash flow models as well as standard valuation analyses, with scenario modeling to stress-test assumptions and surface key value drivers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and manage the M&amp;amp;A and partnership deal pipeline, keeping records current and flagging high-priority opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct initial screening of inbound and proactively sourced targets, assessing strategic fit, deal size, and financial profile against active investment theses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage workstreams end-to-end, coordinating cross-functional teams including Finance, Legal, HR, Tax, and Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare screening memos summarizing key facts, strategic rationale, and recommended next steps for senior review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain presentation materials for leadership and board-level deal reviews, investment committee meetings, and strategic planning discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex financial and strategic analysis into clean, executive-ready decks with clear recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct industry research and competitive landscape analysis to identify emerging opportunities across priority verticals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain diligence trackers, manage the data room, and ensure workstream leads are hitting deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support post-close integration planning and assist with partnership and portfolio reviews, flagging performance trends for leadership attention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-2 years&#39; experience in investment banking, management consulting, private equity, or corporate development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong financial modeling skills; you can build a model from scratch and defend every assumption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional attention to detail; you catch the error before it goes to the CFO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage multiple workstreams simultaneously under tight deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intellectually curious; you&#39;re a fast and eager learner with the demonstrated ability of being a thought partner for strategic decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear, concise written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High proficiency in Excel and Power Point, CapIQ, and AI-based software and tools (Claude, ChatGPT, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
